parameters: \n<Esther><Wrap>"Down by the river... the river so blue..."
\n<Esther><Wrap>You would protect him after what he did?!
\n<Esther><Wrap>After what he did to me?! After what he did to…
\n<Nathan><Wrap>Ahh, he got me good… Bleeding real bad…
\n<Galathan><Wrap>We need to get the King away right now!
\n<Thomas><Wrap>Go, Cap'n. I'll keep this asshole from following.
\n<Galathan><Wrap>Don't be stupid, Thomas! He'll kill you!
\n<Esther><Wrap>All of you will join that bastard of a king!
\n<Thomas><Wrap>Get goin', Cap'n. Don't worry about me. It'll be just like old times.
\n<Galathan><Wrap>Just like old times... Catch up to us, Thomas.
\n<Thomas><Wrap>You didn't give me permission to die, Cap'n. I'll be right along. You go now.
Galathan and the remaining party lead King Alex to safety across the bridge.
\n<Esther><Wrap>Why? We were like brothers, once. All of us.
\nr<Thomas><Wrap>It wasn't his fault, what happened to you. You know the Queen-
\n<Esther><Wrap>He sent my and Lily to die!
\nr<Thomas><Wrap>The King couldn't have ever known what would happen to you there...
\n<Esther><Wrap>"Down by the river... Down by... the river... Down by the river..."
\nr<Thomas><Wrap>Your mind is scrambled... Just like it was that night when you came back. I shoulda killed you then, purely out of mercy. Nate stopped me.
\n<Esther><Wrap>"The river so blue... That's where I fell..."
\nr<Thomas><Wrap>You were our Cap'n once. You don't want to do this. Deep down you know you-
\n<Esther><Wrap>No! Shut up! He killed me! He killed Lily!
\n<Esther><Wrap>Because I couldn't help her! He will answer for what he did to us!
\n<Baenor><Wrap>It might not be the best time or place, but we need to stop here. Nathan is losing a lot of blood, he might not make it if we keep moving.
\n<Nathan><Wrap>I've had worse. We should keep going.
\n<Galathan><Wrap>No, Master Baenor is right, Nate. You need to not be moving, at least for a bit. We will rest here, but only long enough until you can move again.
\n<Baenor><Wrap>I will see to his wounds, Captain.
